Hi guys , I’ve a question about memory leak.
``` public void showLoadingView(boolean shouldShow) {
        getActivity().runOnUiThread(() -&gt;
                progressBar.setVisibility(shouldShow ? View.VISIBLE : View.GONE));
    }```
. I know that  non static inner class and anonymous can cause memory leak in Java. So if I understood well, this following can cause a leak during a configuration change ? or since it’s running on the UI Thread it’s safe ?
